    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Yes, I experience this as well.  Not sure how to fix it yet, but for those joining us the keyboard interrupt is handled in [TerminalInteractiveShell.interact](https://github.com/ipython/ipython/blob/master/IPython/frontend/terminal/interactiveshell.py#L553).\n\nAlso this might be a limitation of readline itself, as it doesn't clear the line buffer on CTRL-C and there isn't an exposed Python interface for changing the line buffer.\n"
