    "created_at": "2013-01-19T07:26:08Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-01-19T07:26:08Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I don't think this is a bug in GNU readline, but a missing feature in Python's readline module.  If we could call `readline.delete_text` in the KeyboardInterrupt branch, then I think we would be set. Unfortunately, Python only exposes a tiny fraction of the readline API, and it includes none at all that let you edit the buffer.\n\nI've seen proposals to add these methods to the stdlib going back before Python 2.3, but it hasn't happened.\n"
